  "text": "Alcohol dependence is a severe and widespread disease. Over 17 million Americans suffer from alcohol-related problems; total cost estimates of substance abuse in the United States exceed $600 billion annually, with 39% of that cost related to alcohol. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] The pharmacotherapies available today are significantly limited due to side effects and failure to relieve drug craving, leading to high relapse rates.",
